    </StandardHierarchyLevel>
    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.6.NS.C.6a</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Recognize opposite signs of numbers as indicating locations on opposite sides of 0 on the number line; recognize that the opposite of the opposite of a number is the number itself, e.g., &amp;ndash;(&amp;ndash;3) = 3, and that 0 is its own opposite.</Statement>
    </Statements>
